# uu_shell_secrets.manifest — secrets the shell processor pulls from the vault.
#
# Format, one per line (whitespace-separated):
#     <device_id> <owner> <vault_key> <ENV_VAR_NAME>
# The processor would export $ENV_VAR_NAME = vault.get_credential(device_id, owner, vault_key),
# cache-first and fail-soft.
#
# Empty today, by design: the vault has no shell-init secrets enumerated yet, and there
# is no vault list-and-export-shell-secrets interface (the missing lever named in
# T-uu-config-profile-layer). Add lines here as secrets move into the vault; the
# processor's vault block reads this file and never blocks shell init on the DB.
#
# Example (commented — not active):
# inference akien OLLAMA_API_KEY OLLAMA_API_KEY
